<article id="post-28597" class="post-28597 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-social-media tag-email-lists tag-kevin-kelly tag-platform tag-social-media tag-true-fans">
	<header class="entry-header">
				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="posted-on">Posted on </span><time class="entry-date updated" datetime="2015-02-16T05:00:56+00:00" pubdate>Monday, February 16, 2015</time>					</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		
		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/true-fans.html" title="Permalink to Why It Takes True Fans to Get the Results You Want" rel="bookmark">Why It Takes True Fans to Get the Results You Want</a></h1>
		<h3 class="getnoticed-entry-subtitle">The Key to Success Is Better Relationships, not Bigger Lists</h3>		
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<aside class='sharebar'>
<span class="share-social share-facebook"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Ftrue-fans.html" class="button" title="Share on Facebook" data-url="http://michaelhyatt.com/true-fans.html" data-threshold="10" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><i></i><span>Share</span></a><span class="count"></span></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-social share-tweet"><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?original_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Ftrue-fans.html&source=tweetbutton&text=Why+It+Takes+True+Fans+to+Get+the+Results+You+Want&url=http%3A%2F%2Fmhyatt.us%2F1Mk65j4&via=michaelhyatt" class="button" title="Tweet this Post" data-url="http://michaelhyatt.com/true-fans.html" data-threshold="10" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><i></i><span>Tweet</span></a><span class="count"></span></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-social share-linkedin"><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Ftrue-fans.html&title=Why+It+Takes+True+Fans+to+Get+the+Results+You+Want&source=Get+Noticed%21+Theme" class="button" title="Share on LinkedIn" data-url="http://michaelhyatt.com/true-fans.html" data-threshold="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><i></i><span>Share</span></a><span class="count"></span></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-social share-buffer"><a href="http://bufferapp.com/add?url=http%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Ftrue-fans.html&text=Why+It+Takes+True+Fans+to+Get+the+Results+You+Want&source=getnoticedtheme&count=vertical" class="button" title="Share with Buffer" data-url="http://michaelhyatt.com/true-fans.html" data-threshold="5" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><i></i><span>Buffer</span></a><span class="count"></span></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-print"><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/true-fans.html#print" class="button"><span>print</span></a></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-email"><a href="mailto:?subject=Why%20It%20Takes%20True%20Fans%20to%20Get%20the%20Results%20You%20Want&amp;body=Hey%2C%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20wanted%20to%20share%20this%20post%20by%20Michael%20Hyatt%20with%20you.%0D%0A%0D%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Ftrue-fans.html%0D%0A%0D%0AThanks%21" class="button"><span>email</span></a></span></aside>
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p class="first-child "><span title="I" class="dropcap">I</span>n our direct-access economy, there are few assets more valuable than a good email list. But what qualifies a list as <em>good</em>?</p>
<p><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/true-fans.html"><img width="760" height="505" src="http://michaelhyatt.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/iStock_000020713249_Medium-760x505.jpg" class="featured-image wp-post-image" alt="iStock_000020713249_Medium" /></a></p><div class="photo-credit">Courtesy of iStock/miappv</div>
<p>The first answer is usually size. We base our value judgment on how many people are on the list. It’s the same for social media metrics. The more the merrier.</p>
<p>But not so fast. Reach is not the same as influence.</p>
	</div>


	
	<footer class="entry-footer entry-meta">

