<article id="post-28524" class="post-28524 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-personal-development tag-brave tag-bravery tag-criticism tag-donald-miller tag-leadership tag-relationships tag-scary-close">
	<header class="entry-header">
				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="posted-on">Posted on </span><time class="entry-date updated" datetime="2015-02-06T05:00:19+00:00" pubdate>Friday, February 6, 2015</time>					</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		
		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/donald-miller-scary-close.html" title="Permalink to What I Learned from Donald Miller about Being Brave" rel="bookmark">What I Learned from Donald Miller about Being Brave</a></h1>
		<h3 class="getnoticed-entry-subtitle">3 Powerful Truths from His New Book ‘Scary Close’</h3>		
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<aside class='sharebar'>
<span class="share-social share-facebook"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Fdonald-miller-scary-close.html" class="button" title="Share on Facebook" data-url="http://michaelhyatt.com/donald-miller-scary-close.html" data-threshold="10" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><i></i><span>Share</span></a><span class="count"></span></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-social share-tweet"><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?original_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Fdonald-miller-scary-close.html&source=tweetbutton&text=What+I+Learned+from+Donald+Miller+about+Being+Brave&url=http%3A%2F%2Fmhyatt.us%2F1zDZNUN&via=michaelhyatt" class="button" title="Tweet this Post" data-url="http://michaelhyatt.com/donald-miller-scary-close.html" data-threshold="10" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><i></i><span>Tweet</span></a><span class="count"></span></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-social share-linkedin"><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Fdonald-miller-scary-close.html&title=What+I+Learned+from+Donald+Miller+about+Being+Brave&source=Get+Noticed%21+Theme" class="button" title="Share on LinkedIn" data-url="http://michaelhyatt.com/donald-miller-scary-close.html" data-threshold="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><i></i><span>Share</span></a><span class="count"></span></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-social share-buffer"><a href="http://bufferapp.com/add?url=http%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Fdonald-miller-scary-close.html&text=What+I+Learned+from+Donald+Miller+about+Being+Brave&source=getnoticedtheme&count=vertical" class="button" title="Share with Buffer" data-url="http://michaelhyatt.com/donald-miller-scary-close.html" data-threshold="5" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><i></i><span>Buffer</span></a><span class="count"></span></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-print"><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/donald-miller-scary-close.html#print" class="button"><span>print</span></a></span>
<span class='sep'> | </span>
<span class="share-email"><a href="mailto:?subject=What%20I%20Learned%20from%20Donald%20Miller%20about%20Being%20Brave&amp;body=Hey%2C%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20wanted%20to%20share%20this%20post%20by%20Michael%20Hyatt%20with%20you.%0D%0A%0D%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Fdonald-miller-scary-close.html%0D%0A%0D%0AThanks%21" class="button"><span>email</span></a></span></aside>
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p class="first-child "><span title="D" class="dropcap">D</span>onald Miller’s newest book, <em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/078521318X/mhyatt-20">Scary Close: Dropping the Act and Finding True Intimacy</a></em>, is out and off to a great start. I can see why. It’s his best book so far.</p>
<p><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/donald-miller-scary-close.html"><img width="760" height="483" src="http://michaelhyatt.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/sc-full-760x483.jpg" class="featured-image wp-post-image" alt="sc-full" /></a></p>
<p>I’ve known Don for over a decade. He was one of our bestselling authors at Thomas Nelson, during the time I was publisher, president, and later CEO. But more than an author, over time he also became a friend—and a teacher.</p>
<p>Don told us about his relationship with God in <em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0785263705/mhyatt-20">Blue Like Jazz</a></em>, which went on to become a huge success. Now, Don tells us about his relationship with relationships. And I hope it becomes a huge success too.</p>
	</div>


	
