<span class="share-email"><a href="mailto:?subject=Season%203%2C%20Episode%2004%3A%20Don%E2%80%99t%20Quit%20Before%20the%20Whistle%20Blows%20%5BPodcast%5D&amp;body=Hey%2C%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20wanted%20to%20share%20this%20post%20by%20Michael%20Hyatt%20with%20you.%0D%0A%0D%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Fmichaelhyatt.com%2Fseason-3-episode-04-dont-quit-before-the-whistle-blows.html%0D%0A%0D%0AThanks%21" class="button"><span>email</span></a></span></aside>
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p class="first-child "><span title="W" class="dropcap">W</span>elcome to <a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/podcast-season-3" title="This Is Your Life Season 3">Season 3</a>, Episode 4 of the <em><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/podcast-season-3" title="This Is Your Life Season 3">This Is Your Life</a></em> podcast. In this second episode, <a href="http://michelecushatt.com/" title="Michele Cushatt’s Website">Michele Cushatt</a> and I discuss why we should play full out, especially when we feel like giving up.</p>
<p><a href="http://michaelhyatt.com/season-3-episode-04-dont-quit-before-the-whistle-blows.html"><img width="760" height="380" src="http://michaelhyatt.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Season-3-Episode-4-Artwork-V1-760x380.jpg" class="featured-image wp-post-image" alt="Season-3-Episode-4-Artwork-V1" /></a></p>
<p>Anyone can start something. But after we begin a new project, goal, or relationship, a million things come up and it’s easy to drop out. Here are three truths to keep in mind when you’re not sure you can finish.</p>
<h3>Listen to the Audio</h3>
<div class="powerpress_player" id="powerpress_player_4066"><object type="application/x-shockwave-flash" data="http://michaelhyatt.com/wp-content/plugins/powerpress/audio-player.swf" id="4066" height="24" width="570">
